00:15:26,109 --> 00:15:27,690
for a long time, but it's super good.

292
00:15:28,510 --> 00:15:31,991
So this is a very, very simple real-time puzzle game

293
00:15:32,111 --> 00:15:34,512
where you're trying to build and service

294
00:15:34,772 --> 00:15:38,873
a continually growing network of subway stations.

295
00:15:39,974 --> 00:15:41,154
So you have some limited resources

296
00:15:41,194 --> 00:15:44,615
in terms of carriages and lines and trains, bridges.

297
00:15:46,832 --> 00:15:48,994
But you have an ever-growing pile of passengers

298
00:15:50,034 --> 00:15:52,777
and an ever-growing number of stations.

299
00:15:52,837 --> 00:15:55,219
And you need to keep trying to find the best fit solution.

300
00:15:55,659 --> 00:15:57,321
And then the game does gorgeous things

301
00:15:57,381 --> 00:16:00,924
about drawing and routing the train lines that you're

302
00:16:00,944 --> 00:16:06,088
putting in place as if it were as a real beautiful map.

303
00:16:09,420 --> 00:16:15,622
And to help you do that well, you can speed up and slow down time, as is often the case in games of this sort.

304
00:16:16,263 --> 00:16:20,785
But they just quietly hide that UI in the top right.

305
00:16:21,485 --> 00:16:26,687
So if you tap on the clock, those controls drop down, then they go away again.

306
00:16:29,488 --> 00:16:31,529
With a really lovely treatment on the clock.

307
00:16:33,109 --> 00:16:35,029
where the clock is doing, the clock is great,

308
00:16:35,069 --> 00:16:37,630
it's a button that's also a status readout

309
00:16:37,650 --> 00:16:39,411
of whether it's day or night,

310
00:16:39,571 --> 00:16:41,432
and it's also your time readout

311
00:16:41,452 --> 00:16:44,553
in terms of how fast time is passing,

312
00:16:45,153 --> 00:16:46,934
and it also shows you whether or not time is paused.

313
00:16:47,394 --> 00:16:49,315
And it does all of that in a lovely little circle

314
00:16:49,755 --> 00:16:51,856
that is also a cute joke about the famous

315
00:16:52,476 --> 00:16:54,437
Swiss railway clock design that

316
00:16:57,688 --> 00:17:00,369
rail design people love to make jokes about.

317
00:17:01,009 --> 00:17:03,530
It's super simple, but this game would feel,

318
00:17:03,671 --> 00:17:04,471
if it loops around again,

319
00:17:04,771 --> 00:17:05,951
this game would feel so different

320
00:17:06,192 --> 00:17:10,053
if that whole right-hand wall was just blocked off

321
00:17:10,113 --> 00:17:11,314
all the time with all of those icons.

322
00:17:11,374 --> 00:17:14,175
It needs that space to give you that curve

323
00:17:14,275 --> 00:17:15,535
in the top corner so much.

324
00:17:16,996 --> 00:17:19,137
This game has a bunch of really nice tricks up its sleeve.

325
00:17:19,457 --> 00:17:20,637
I haven't got time to talk about them all today,

326
00:17:20,717 --> 00:17:22,618
but the way it handles.

327
00:17:23,922 --> 00:17:25,143
What happens to you when you lose,

328
00:17:25,423 --> 00:17:26,643
which is a thing you'll find out very quickly

329
00:17:26,663 --> 00:17:27,503
when you try it for the first time.

330
00:17:27,703 --> 00:17:28,704
This is really nicely handled.

331
00:17:29,684 --> 00:17:32,605
So, R&E tip number one, hide.

332
00:17:32,625 --> 00:17:34,145
It's a good way of making space.

333
00:17:36,206 --> 00:17:38,226
R&E tip number two, merge.

334
00:17:39,307 --> 00:17:40,007
By which I mean,

335
00:17:42,087 --> 00:17:46,869
you'll remember that the absolute crucial maneuver

336
00:17:47,109 --> 00:17:48,509
in Predator was that he discovered

337
00:17:48,569 --> 00:17:50,710
if he glooped himself all the way into the mud,

338
00:17:51,630 --> 00:17:52,610
then the Predator couldn't see him.

